      "comment": "PORT FERDINAND (4) had to dig deep on debut when scoring a 1400m contest at Naas. That trip was always going to be on the sharp side and now steps up in distance and should take beating. LIMESTONE (2) has a tongue strap fitted on the return to the track having scored on heavy ground at Listowel in September. No surprise if he goes and gets a second win. MR VETTORI (3) is a well-bred son of Lope De Vega who won impressively on his final start at Gowran Park in October. Highly rated. SUMMER IS TOMORROW (1) is the stablemate of LIMESTONE and second choice on jockey bookings. Looks to be up against it.",
